HEADWORD: Petrology
<hw>Pe*trol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Petro</ets>
+ <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The department of science
which is concerned with the mineralogical and chemical composition of
rocks, and with their classification: lithology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A treatise on petrology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petromastoid</ent>⟦br⟧
